self does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Mordaunt was born in 1236, in Turvey, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Mordaunt, was 37 and his mother, Amicia De Olney, was 22. He married Rose Wake about 1266, in Turvey, Bedfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1236–":"1236–Surnud","1236–Male":"1236–Surnud","1252–1327":"1252–1327","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1264–1355":"1264–1355","1267–Male":"1267–Surnud","1200–1279":"1200–1279","1214–1294":"1214–1294","1264":"1264","About 1235":"umbes 1235","1252":"1252","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1327":"1327","1236":"1236","1214":"1214","1279":"1279","1267":"1267","1355":"1355","1200":"1200","about 1266":"umbes 1266","about 1267":"umbes 1267","about 1264":"umbes 1264","Turvey, Bedfordshire, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, England","Olney, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1236–":"1236–Kuollut","1236–Male":"1236–Kuollut","1252–1327":"1252–1327","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1264–1355":"1264–1355","1267–Male":"1267–Kuollut","1200–1279":"1200–1279","1214–1294":"1214–1294","1264":"1264","About 1235":"noin 1235","1252":"1252","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1327":"1327","1236":"1236","1214":"1214","1279":"1279","1267":"1267","1355":"1355","1200":"1200","about 1266":"noin 1266","about 1267":"noin 1267","about 1264":"noin 1264","Turvey, Bedfordshire, England":"Turvey, Bedfordshire, England","Olney, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1236–":"1236–Décédé","1236–Male":"1236–Décédé","1252–1327":"1252–1327","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","12